headline: Cboe CEO: Sports Prediction Not a Focus Right Now
summary: Craig Donohue, CEO of Cboe Global Markets, says the company has expanded access for customers interested in shorter-term contracts with capped risk. He tells Romaine Bostick and Katie Greifeld on "The Close" that while he sees explosive growth in the sports prediction market, sports betting is not a focus for the firm.

headline: Cboe CEO on Getting Into Prediction Markets
summary: Craig Donohue, CEO of Cboe Global Markets, says the options trading giant is interested in breaking into event and prediction markets, but says sports will not be the focus.

headline: Tradr Launches Leveraged ETFs on Bloom Energy, Celestica, NANO Nuclear & Synopsys
summary: Tradr ETFs, a provider of ETFs designed for sophisticated investors and professional traders, today launched four new single stock leveraged ETFs. The funds seek to deliver twice (200%) the daily performance of a specific underlying stock. Listed on Cboe, these ETFs are the first and only strategies available for this group of growth-oriented companies.
